Deploys:
  ✓ pnpm sst deploy --stage production rolled out G.1 + G.2 + G.3
    code; ECS service basics-runtime-api-production rolled over
    to task definition :103 (verified via aws ecs describe-services).

Bug caught LIVE during G.4 (real correctness fix, not in any test):
  - public.approvals was NOT in the supabase_realtime publication.
    The G.1 approvals SSE route subscribed successfully but never
    received any postgres_changes payloads — only the hydrate
    frame ever arrived. cloud_activity WAS in the publication (so
    G.3 outputs SSE worked on first try).
  - FIX: applied migration `automations_g4_approvals_realtime_
    publication` via Supabase MCP, idempotent ALTER PUBLICATION
    supabase_realtime ADD TABLE public.approvals. Mirrored to
    api/drizzle/0029_approvals_realtime_publication.sql + journal
    idx 29.
  - After the fix, the second test run (v2) captured both the
    INSERT (pending) and UPDATE (approved+decided_via='desktop')
    frames as expected.

